#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:3
msgid "Nix language basics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:5
msgid ""
"The Nix language is designed for conveniently creating and composing "
"*derivations* – precise descriptions of how contents of existing files are "
"used to derive new files. It is a domain-specific, purely functional, lazily "
"evaluated, dynamically typed programming language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:8
msgid "Notable uses of the Nix language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:13
msgid "{term}`Nixpkgs`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:15
msgid ""
"The largest, most up-to-date software distribution in the world, and written "
"in the Nix language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:17
msgid "{term}`NixOS`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:19
msgid ""
"A Linux distribution that can be configured fully declaratively and is based "
"on Nix and Nixpkgs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:21
msgid ""
"Its underlying modular configuration system is written in the Nix language, "
"and uses packages from Nixpkgs. The operating system environment and "
"services it provides are configured with the Nix language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:25
msgid ""
"You may quickly encounter Nix language expressions that look very "
"complicated. As with any programming language, the required amount of Nix "
"language code closely matches the complexity of the problem it is supposed "
"to solve, and reflects how well the problem – and its solution – is "
"understood. Building software is a complex undertaking, and Nix both "
"*exposes* and *allows managing* this complexity with the Nix language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:29
msgid ""
"Yet, the Nix language itself has only a few basic concepts that will be "
"introduced in this tutorial, and which can be combined arbitrarily. What may "
"look complicated comes not from the language, but from how it is used."
msgstr ""

