#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:145
msgid "Evaluating Nix files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:147
msgid ""
"Use [`nix-instantiate --eval`][nix-instantiate] to evaluate the expression "
"in a Nix file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:149
msgid ""
"$ echo 1 + 2 > file.nix\n"
"$ nix-instantiate --eval file.nix\n"
"3\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:0
msgid "Detailed explanation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:157
msgid ""
"The first command writes `1 + 2` to a file `file.nix` in the current "
"directory. The contents of `file.nix` are now `1 + 2`, which you can check "
"with"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:160
msgid ""
"$ cat file.nix\n"
"1 + 2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:165
msgid ""
"The second command runs `nix-instantiate` with the `--eval` option on `file."
"nix`, which reads the file and evaluates the contained Nix expression. The "
"resulting value is printed as output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:168
msgid ""
"`--eval` is required to evaluate the file and do nothing else. If `--eval` "
"is omitted, `nix-instantiate` expects the expression in the given file to "
"evaluate to a special value called a *derivation*, which we will come back "
"to at the end of this tutorial in [](derivations)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:174
msgid ""
"`nix-instantiate --eval` will try to read from `default.nix` if no file name "
"is specified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:176
msgid ""
"$ echo 1 + 2 > default.nix\n"
"$ nix-instantiate --eval\n"
"3\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:184
msgid ""
"The Nix language uses lazy evaluation, and `nix-instantiate` by default only "
"computes values when needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:186
msgid ""
"Some examples show a fully evaluated data structure for clarity. If your "
"output does not match the example, try adding the `--strict` option to `nix-"
"instantiate`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:191
msgid ""
"$ echo \"{ a.b.c = 1; }\" > file.nix\n"
"$ nix-instantiate --eval file.nix\n"
"{ a = <CODE>; }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:197
msgid ""
"$ echo \"{ a.b.c = 1; }\" > file.nix\n"
"$ nix-instantiate --eval --strict file.nix\n"
"{ a = { b = { c = 1; }; }; }\n"
msgstr ""

