#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:2083
msgid ""
"If you worked through the examples, you will have noticed that reading the "
"Nix language reveals the structure of the code, but does not necessarily "
"tell what the code actually means."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:2085
msgid "Often it is not possible to determine from the code at hand"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:2086
msgid "the data type of a named value or function argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nix-language.md:2087
